==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Prestation
<hw>Pres*ta"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>praestatio</ets> a performing, paying, fr. <ets>praestare</ets>:
cf. F. <ets>prestation</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(O. Eng. Law)</fld> <def>A
payment of money; a toll or duty; also, the rendering of a
service.</def> <rj><au>Burrill.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><-- p. 1134 --></p>

<p><cs><col><b>Prestation money</b></col>, <cd>a sum of money paid
yearly by archdeacons and other dignitaries to their
bishop.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Prester</ent>⟦br⟧
